			<ns0:name>mcgra...@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/109286297231979736865/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">The scheme for adding sandboxing instructions to load/store instructions doesn't apply the same predicate bits to the masking instruction as are used in the load or store.  If the base register is ever used for a non-address in the predicate-false case, that register's value could be corrupted.

Such code has never been observed and we speculate it's unlikely that it will be produced.  Still, ideally we should make sure that the whole sequence gets the same predicate.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2013-02-08T22:22:14.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-12-20T00:12:32.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
